author: CHRIS GARRY
title: Broncos release Gavet from contract
text:
James Gavet has been released by the Broncos.
CHRIS GARRY The Courier-Mail HE was meant to be Brisbaneâ€™s enforcer, but James Gavet has been released from his Broncos contract a year early after playing just one game for the club.
A bruising forward signed from Wests Tigers late in 2014, Gavet played the opening round match for Brisbane then tore his ACL at training the following week and missed the entire season.
The Broncos also released another one game player in 20-year-old outside back Jordan Drew.
Drew has signed with Cronulla for two seasons. He played one game for Brisbane in 2013 as an 18-year-old, scoring a try in the 26-24 victory over St George Illawarra.
Brisbane will this morning announce a new major sponsor, a deal understood to be a significant coup for the club.
